4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE REGISTERED
5 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM; REVISING DUTIES OF THE DEPARTMENT OF LABOR AND INDUSTRY
6 FOR THE REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM; REVISING ALLOWABLE CREDIT FOR PRIOR
7 TRAINING OR EXPERIENCE; CLARIFYING VOLUNTARY PARTICIPATION OF EMPLOYERS IN THE
8 REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM AND ITS PROVISIONS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 39-6-
9 101, 39-6-103, 39-6-106, AND 39-6-107, MCA.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 39-6-101, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "39-6-101. Duties of department -- definitions. (1) The department shall:
15 (a) encourage and promote the making of apprenticeship agreements conforming to the standards
16 established by or in accordance with this chapter;
17 (b) register apprenticeship agreements that are in the best interests of the apprenticeship and
18 conform to the standards established by or in accordance with this chapter;
19 (c) keep a record of apprenticeship agreements and, taking into consideration performance of the
20 agreement, issue certificates of completion of apprenticeship;
21 (d) terminate or cancel any apprenticeship agreements in accordance with the provisions of the
22 agreements;
23 (e) provide assistance for the development of on-the-job training programs in nonapprenticeable
24 occupations;
25 (f) (e) establish standards for apprenticeship agreements in conformity with the provisions of this
26 chapter;
27 (g) (f) use the standard prevailing wage rate for construction services, as defined in 18-2-401, for a
28 prevailing wage rate district as provided in 18-2-411 as a base on which an apprenticeship wage is calculated
