1 pursuant to 39-6-108 for apprentices;
2 (h) (g) adopt rules necessary to carry out the intent and purposes of this chapter; and
3 (i) (h) perform other duties that may be required by federal regulations, provided that the federal
4 regulations are not in conflict with this chapter.
5 (2) At least once every 2 years, the department shall report on its activities and findings to the
6 governor and, as provided in 5-11-210, to the legislature. The department shall also make the report available
7 to the public.
8 (3) For the purposes of this chapter, the following definitions apply:
9 (a) "Apprentice" means a worker employed to learn a skilled occupation under a written
10 apprenticeship agreement registered with the department.
11 (b) "Department" means the department of labor and industry."
12
13 Section 2. Section 39-6-103, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "39-6-103. Responsibilities of state and local boards responsible for vocational education.
15 Related and supplemental instruction for apprentices, coordination of instruction with job experiences, and the
16 selection and training of teachers and coordinators for such the instruction shall be the responsibility of state
17 and local boards that are responsible for vocational education in collaboration with the state apprenticeship
18 agency. State and local boards may utilize subject matter experts and national programs in providing related
19 and supplemental instruction."
20
21 Section 3. Section 39-6-106, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "39-6-106. Contents of apprenticeship agreements -- credit for prior training or experience. (1)
23 Apprenticeship agreements must contain:
24 (a) a statement of the occupation to be taught and the required hours for completion of
25 apprenticeship, which must be at least 2,000 hours of reasonably continuous employment;
26 (b) a statement of the processes in the occupational divisions in which the apprentice is to be
27 taught and the approximate amount of time to be spent at each process;
28 (c) a statement of the number of hours to be spent by the apprentice in related and supplemental
